cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a decentralised framework for swarm distribution guidance, which involves homogeneous agents working together towards a common goal. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the proposed framework can be applied to robotic swarms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a closed-loop control framework for swarm distribution guidance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the proposed framework uses feedback gains from the current swarm status to generate stochastic policies. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the proposed framework involves learning from local information to achieve a desired density distribution.
